<https://w3id.org/mqto#ActuableProperty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An actuable property of an ActualIshikawaItem that can be controlled or modified via Actuations. As a subclass of mqto:Property, it implements a Signal specification from the specified layer. Represents properties that can be set or modified, such as setpoints, valve positions, motor speeds, or control commands. The Signal in the specified layer defines the control channel metadata, while ActuableProperty represents the actual controllable quality of a specific feature of interest."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#ActuableProperty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Actuable Property"@en .
