<https://w3id.org/mqto#IshikawaItem> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Abstract superclass for the three categories of root causes in an Ishikawa (fishbone) diagram: Machine, Material, and Method. In die-casting ontologies (dg.ttl), this pattern is instantiated with dg:Aggregate (equivalent to Machine), dg:Material, and dg:Process (equivalent to Method), plus dg:Product (output of manufacturing, no direct mqto equivalent)."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#IshikawaItem> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Ishikawa Item"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#List
<https://w3id.org/mqto#List> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#List> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An ordered, reusable container of CountermeasureSteps within the specified layer. Modelled as a linked list (mqto:first / mqto:rest) so that step order is external to the step instances, allowing steps to be shared across different Countermeasure procedures. The list is terminated by mqto:nil."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#List> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "List"@en .
# 
