<https://w3id.org/mqto#ObservableProperty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An observable property of an ActualIshikawaItem that can be measured via Observations. As a subclass of mqto:Property, it implements a Signal specification from the specified layer, establishing traceability from actual observations back to the specified data channel definition. Note: subclassing both sosa:ObservableProperty (an abstract quality type) and lis:Actual (via mqto:Property, a concrete instance) reflects the modelling choice that each mqto:ObservableProperty individual represents a specific, concrete observable quality tied to a particular actual item — not a reusable abstract type. This parallels how sosa:ObservableProperty instances are used in practice (e.g. 'the temperature of this specific machine part') rather than as universal property types."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#ObservableProperty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Observable Property"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#Observation
<https://w3id.org/mqto#Observation> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#Observation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/sosa/Observation> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#Observation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Subclass of sosa:Observation, representing a single sensor reading or measurement event. Links to an ActualIshikawaItem (feature of interest), an ObservableProperty (what is being measured), and a Result (the measured value). In die-casting (dga ontology), observations capture time-series data from PLCs, sensors, and SCADA systems - e.g., furnace temperature readings, die pressure measurements, cycle times."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#Observation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Observation"@en .
