<https://w3id.org/mqto#ProcessExecution> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Actual execution of a Method, the instance-layer counterpart of Method. Links to concrete PhysicalMachines and MaterialChunks as participants. In die-casting (dga ontology), this represents actual production shots with specific machines, material batches, timestamps, and observation data. Note: ProcessExecution does not directly subclass lis:Activity (which is lis:Specified), but instead subclasses ActualIshikawaItem (lis:Actual) and implements Method (which is lis:Activity). This maintains the LIS distinction between specified and actual layers."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#ProcessExecution> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Process Execution"@en .
