<https://w3id.org/mqto#Property> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Actual-layer counterpart of Signal. Represents a property (observable or actuable) of an ActualIshikawaItem that implements a Signal specification from the specified layer. While Signal defines the data channel metadata (identifier, unit, sampling rate, direction), Property represents the actual measured or actuated quality of a specific feature of interest. This class serves as the abstract superclass for both ObservableProperty (for sensing/measurement) and ActuableProperty (for actuation/control)."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#Property> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Property"@en .
